narratives.question_text: Please rate and comment on the following aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: Workload
comments: No extra work - just enough so that we can share our learnings communally.

The workload is moderate, and solely depends on how much you are willing to dig into the organization you're working on. It is very helpful that the students have access to previous presentation materials to build upon.

narratives.question_text: Please comment on all aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: Organization.Comments:
comments: Increasingly complex lectures led to deeper discussions in our own presentations.

The structure of this course, in comparison, is not as clear as the other course given by the same instructor. There were also some confusion about the handout, and for some sessions students were not distributed course materials.

narratives.question_text: Please comment on all aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: the Instructor.Comments:
comments: I feel like we didn't cover all the material we intended to, and had to rush through some material, because of the pacing of the class. It was frustrating not to receive feedback on work in a timely manner.
The instructor's charisma successfully held the class together, and his guidance to in-depth discussions was beneficiary to the whole class.

narratives.question_text: Please comment on: Visitors, if any
Please comment on all aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: Your Learning.Comments:
comments: Harder to enumerate the things I learned - complex concepts with lots and lots of "aha" moments.
It would be helpful if all presentation materials can be find on V2, which would make it easier for students to have a clear understanding of which page they're on in terms of the overall course.
